<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-15T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2987:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-15T12:00:00+01:00">May 15,
                                    1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 15—9:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>666. For the President. Coulondre, former French Ambassador in Berlin,
                            called on me this morning to add another appeal for the French
                            Government for airplanes from the United States. The wastage in the
                            present battle at Sedan is so enormous that a time is foreseen about a
                            month hence when any kind of a plane that can take the air will be
                            better than none.</p>
                        <p>Is there nothing in the way of obsolete planes of our Army or Navy that
                            can possibly be procured?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>